$ /etc/X11/default-display-manager

At least in Debian, `→ Linux/fhs/etc/X11[/etc/X11]/default-display-manager` contains the path to the executable of the
→ Linux/X/display-manager, for example `/usr/sbin/gdm3`.

→ https://unix.stackexchange.com/a/20376[Compare with] `/etc/sysconfig/desktop` (Red Hat, Fedora) and `/etc/sysconfig/displaymanager` (OpenSuSe).

sa:

code {
→ Linux/shell/commands/grep ExecStart= → Linux/fhs/etc/systemd/system/display-manager_service
code }
